) by the combination of black femora, slightly larger size (WL = 3.5–4), and different host plant (
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E1973544FFE4FC6E8AC651CDD192" box="[953,1224,1721,1747]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Elaeagnaceae" genus="Hippophae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="10" pageNumber="463" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhamnoides">
<emphasis id="ABD046063544FFE4FC6E8AC651CDD192" box="[953,1224,1721,1747]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">Hippophae rhamnoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E1973544FFE4FEE48AA654A7D1B2" box="[307,418,1753,1779]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Rhamnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="10" pageNumber="463" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ABD046063544FFE4FEE48AA654A7D1B2" box="[307,418,1753,1779]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">Rhamnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E1973544FFE4FE1D8AA5573CD1B2" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[458,569,1754,1779]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="463" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ABD046063544FFE4FE1D8AA5573CD1B2" box="[458,569,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">Juniperus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). We have seen no material from 
<collectingCountry id="E1B3DA843544FFE4FC1A8AA65152D1B5" box="[973,1111,1753,1780]" name="Switzerland" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry id="E1B3DA843544FFE4FB578AA651C1D1B5" box="[1152,1220,1753,1780]" name="Spain" pageId="10" pageNumber="463">Spain</collectingCountry>
, and records from these countries need verification by reexamination of specimens.
